the apostolic vicariate of anatolia (latin: vicariatus apostolicus anatoliensis) is a roman catholic latin apostolic vicariate, in the eastern half of anatolia (asian turkey). the missionary pre-diocesan jurisdiction is exempt, i.e. directly dependent on the holy see (notably the roman congregation for the oriental churches, unusual for a latin see), not part of any ecclesiastical province. its cathedral episcopal see is the marian cathedral of the annunciation, in iÌ‡skenderun (alexandria). it also has a co-cathedral of st. anthony of padua, in mersin.